**Risks (behavior-preservation traps):**
- --FORCE SILENCE (round-3 regression, blocker 1): the refspec phase must be force-gated so it emits ZERO lines under --force in every case except the explicit-missing error — no skip-note, no configure. Strengthened TestInitForceMissingDefaultOriginSucceeds asserts the note is ABSENT.
- DRY-RUN COUNT FIDELITY (blockers 2+3): write actions os.Stat to preview create-vs-skip so counts match a real run in fresh AND populated repos; the refspec preview respects force (force+present -> 0 to configure per directive D; !force+present -> 2; absent -> 0, no error). TestInitDryRunExistingScaffoldSkips + TestInitForceDryRun lock these.
- WRITE-THEN-ERROR: refspec-phase action runs in apply() AFTER write actions; absent+remoteChanged returns error after writes. TestInitExplicitMissingRemoteWritesThenErrors asserts post-error file existence.
- dry-run is READ-ONLY: actions touch only os.Stat / remoteExists in dryRun; writeScaffoldFile / addRefspecIfAbsent / git config --add are never reached. TestInitDryRunExistingRemoteNoAdd locks no-add.
- Status->bucket: configured = statusConfigured + statusAlreadyConfigured; statusNote uncounted; identical mapping for normal and dry-run so counts never diverge.
- Shared string consts keep apply output and dry-run reporting from drifting; five legacy strings byte-identical.
- Refspec add-if-absent semantics (verified git 2.47.1): `git remote add` auto-seeds remote.<n>.fetch (fetch -> value-compare/already-configured branch), push -> get-all exit-1 empty branch; `git remote get-url` exits 2 for missing. addRefspecIfAbsent keeps calling gitGetAll unchanged; only its print/return shape changes.
- Deterministic ordering (workflow.yaml -> rubrics -> refspec phase) keeps dry-run lines + counts stable; stderr empty on success (summary on stdout).
- Existing tests use strings.Contains, not full-buffer equality, so the trailing summary line is safe.

